Nomzamo Yuku  A fire in Imizamo Yethu Informal Settlement in Hout Bay
gutted three houses and an undisclosed number of shacks today (Wednesday 22
August) at about 13:25. Theo Layne, spokesperson for City of Cape Town Fire and
Rescue Services, says officials attended to the incident. He says four fire
engines, one water tanker and a rescue vehicle with 24 firefighters was
dispatched. A resident, Ziyanda Nguqu say it is believed the fire
started in a backyard shack and spread to the three other houses in Chris Hani
Road. Watch homes burning in the video below.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  